=======
Quamash
=======
Implementation of the [PEP 3156 Event-Loop](http://legacy.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3156/) with Qt
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
:author: Mark Harviston <mark.harviston@gmail.com>, Arve Knudsen <arve.knudsen@gmail.com>

Usage
=====

.. code:: python

    import quamash
    import time
    import asyncio
    import sys
    import logging

    try:
        from PyQt5.QtWidgets import QApplication, QMainWindow
    except ImportError:
        from PySide.QtGui import QApplication, QMainWindow

    def identity(x):
        time.sleep(10)
        return x

    @asyncio.coroutine
    def my_task(loop):
        for x in range(5):
            y = yield from loop.run_in_executor(None, identity, x)
            assert x == y

        loop.stop()

    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)
    _logger = logging.getLogger('App')

    if __name__ == '__main__':
        app = QApplication(sys.argv)

        win = QMainWindow()
        win.show()

        loop = quamash.QEventLoop(app)
        with loop:
            loop.call_soon(my_task, loop)

            loop.run_forever()


Name
====
Tulip related projects are being named after other flowers, Quamash is one of the few flowers that starts with a "Q".

